column5: I know how you feel I'm not saying a word
While our trip is still a few months away....dang I am stoked. In all reality its only a couple busy weekends of honey dues right
What to do to pass the time, I guess thumb through the tackle box a few more times
I find myself studying the contour maps on Navionicshttp://www.navionics.com/en/webapp

Yup. Went through the tackle box again yesterday and the jointed black and silver Rapala was missing. Gotta find that. Sharpened my filet knife again on Tuesday and cut my finger again while doing it. This will surprise absolutely no one who knows me. Sending daily ridiculous emails to the fishing crew with dumb menu suggestions and scathing insults. Good idea there. Need to keep doing that one. Especially the insults. Yup, getting a bit antsy for the fishing trip.

Have ya ever filleted your finger instead of the fish because the fillet glove was on the hand holding the knife????? Don't ask how I know, but somehow I think the left brain felt like there would be a much better grip on that knife with the fillet glove. Apparently the right brain got ate up with dumb dumbs.....at that particular moment..... PjShorthorn

My wife and I are going on a trip to Cancun without the kids, all-inclusive at a 5 star resort the first week of June to celebrate our 15th anniversary. I'm more excited about the trip to Ontario in August. Don't tell her that though.
Dude hippa does not cover WC! My silence can be bought however! You have that open seat..... I think we could work out a deal eh!!!!
